obo:GO_0098978  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1896  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: Rheb regulates spine synapse formation.\n(a) Dendrites of EGFP- and mock- or FLAG-RhebQ64V-expressing hippocampal neurons prepared from WT and Tsc2+/- rats at DIV 19. Neurons were co-immunostained with anti-GFP and vGlut1 antibodies. Scale bar, 10μm. (b, c) Cumulative probability distributions of protrusion width (b) and length (c) in (a). RhebQ64V-expressing WT neurons showed narrower (D = 0.2690, P < 0.001) and longer (D = 0.2391, P < 0.001) dendritic protrusions than mock transfectants (Kolmogorov-Smirnov test). (d) Quantification of the spine synapse densities shown in (a).. Experimental description: Primary culture and transfection of hippocampal neurons from Tsc2+/- and WT littermates (E20)\nCultured hippocampal neurons\n\n13/11/2017 PIM\n- Species of overexpressed protein is not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted (yamagata-kn@igakuken.or.jp, dd 13/11/2017). Authors responded:\n\n\"Dear Dr. van Nierop,\n\nWe are sorry we forgot to describe the species. We used rat rheb cDNA in that paper.\n\nBest regards,\nKanato\"\n\n- Rat species was selected based on the species of the overexpressed protein." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1896" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

